  "description": "Viscoplasticity is also modeled in FLAC3D or 3DEC by combining the viscoelastic WIPP model with the elasto-plastic Drucker-Prager model . Of the plasticity models currently embodied in FLAC3D / 3DEC , the Drucker-Prager model is the most compatible with the WIPP model , because both models are formulated in terms of the second invariant of the deviatoric stress tensor. Viewed in the \\(\\pi\\) -plane, both models exhibit responses that depend only on radial distance from the isotropic-stress locus. The response of the Mohr-Coulomb model , on the other hand, is not isotropic, because the intermedi",
